text: Your video is wonderful. Many thanks to you Faisal. You made a great video. But Tatas were way ahead in their Nano project and they worked on costs using reverse engineering. This 2019 Bajaj baby Qute looks like a model from 80s era. Nano was a far better car or should I say it was the best in its category.  Indeed it created its own category. Unfortunately for Nano, Mamta Didi played with the initial Nano project in Bengal and the then transport and road division said they are unable to cope up with huge demand for Nano and so they asked Tatas to reduce the manufacturing, fearing too many Nanos on the street. This all went against a wonderful Nano which would have been improved in many ways from sports version to a premium version by now. This Bajaj Qute a poor mans mini Wagon R looking car is actually a tempo (who else uses slider windows and no AC option?) Bajaj Qute is totally unsafe.
